The article discusses the strong relationship between the United States and Spain. The two countries work together on various global challenges, such as promoting international cooperation, peace, security, and economic prosperity. They have a strong security cooperation, with Spain allowing the United States to use its air and naval bases for military purposes. Spain is also involved in counterterrorism efforts and participates in international missions around the world. The economic ties between the two countries are robust, with Spain being a significant investor in the United States and American companies employing many Spaniards. There is also a strong cultural exchange between the U.S. and Spain, with educational and cultural programs supporting the exchange of students and scholars between the two countries.